\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces  Render time normalised by the full-payload render time for each block. The close alignment of the block curves indicates that the relative payload-scaling behaviour is consistent across the five pretrained representations. The dashed reference indicates ideal linear scaling with retained Gaussian percentage. }}{8}{figure.caption.9}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:rq1_normalised_scaling}{{5}{8}{Render time normalised by the full-payload render time for each block. The close alignment of the block curves indicates that the relative payload-scaling behaviour is consistent across the five pretrained representations. The dashed reference indicates ideal linear scaling with retained Gaussian percentage}{figure.caption.9}{}}
